President Obama announced his intent to nominate four individuals for key administration posts. Jeffrey Feltman was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Near Eastern Affairs at the Department of State. Charles A. Hurley was nominated for Administrator of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration at the Department of Transportation. Robert O. Work was nominated for Under Secretary of the Navy at the Department of the Navy. Charles A. Blanchard was nominated for General Counsel at the Department of the Air Force. President Obama expressed confidence in their skills and dedication, and he looks forward to working with them to keep the nation safe.